 :tx/rationale "Create task: META-8: R(t) continuous weight learning from coherence deltas. BACKGROUND: R(t) currently requires 50+ explicit outcome classifications before weight learning begins. With metabolic deltas, every transaction IS an outcome signal. If agent followed R(t) recommendation and subsequent transactions have high positive coherence-delta, the recommendation was good. If they have low delta, it was wasted. APPROACH: In guidance.rs compute_routing/refit_routing_weights: (1) After recording an action entity (:action/recommended-command), track the next N transactions' delta values. (2) Outcome signal = mean(delta-crystallization + delta-implementation + delta-verification) for transactions within 5 minutes of action. (3) If outcome > 0.1: classify as 'followed+productive'. If outcome < -0.05: classify as 'followed+counterproductive'. If no transactions within window: classify as 'ignored'. (4) Feed into existing weight learning pipeline (refit_routing_weights). (5) This provides continuous training data — every session generates 10-50 outcome signals instead of requiring manual classification. ACCEPTANCE: (A) R(t) weight learning activates after 30 metabolic outcomes (instead of 50 manual). (B) Weight updates correlate with coherence improvement. (C) Existing routing tests pass (backward-compatible). DEPENDS-ON: META-5 (t-ba14c7a9) for full three-vector. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs. TRACES TO: INV-GUIDANCE-010 (R(t) routing), INV-GUIDANCE-008 (M(t) methodology score)."
